              },
              "name": "Player Core",
              "page": 453,
              "type": "source"
            }
          ],
          "text": "A creature similar to an animal but with an Intelligence modifier of \u20133 or higher is usually a beast. Unlike an animal, a beast might be able to speak and reason.",
          "type": "trait"
        },
        {
          "alternate_link": {
            "alternate_type": "legacy",
            "aonid": 299,
            "game-obj": "Traits",
            "type": "alternate_link"
          },
          "classes": [
            "creature_type"
          ],
          "edition": "remastered",
          "game-id": "54c71b87a41f627b517762bbaefeca02",
          "game-obj": "Traits",
          "name": "Dream",
          "sources": [
            {
              "errata": {
                "alt": "2.0",
                "aonid": 218,
                "game-obj": "Sources",
                "name": "2.0",
                "type": "link"
              },
              "link": {
                "alt": "GM Core pg. 328",
                "aonid": 218,
                "game-obj": "Sources",
                "name": "GM Core pg. 328",
                "type": "link"
              },
              "name": "GM Core",
              "page": 328,
              "type": "source"
            }
          ],
          "text": "Creatures native to the Dimension of Dreams can possess a diverse array of abilities, although those associated with the nightmare realm of Leng are almost always unholy and immune to that realm\u2019s freezing temperatures.",
          "type": "trait"
        },
        {
          "classes": [
            "monsters"
          ],
          "edition": "remastered",
          "game-id": "40b5d9c5e49dbe2aea5d7ecf38d950f3",
          "game-obj": "Traits",
          "name": "Mythic",
          "sources": [
            {
              "link": {
                "alt": "War of Immortals pg. 69",
                "aonid": 232,
                "game-obj": "Sources",
                "name": "War of Immortals pg. 69",
                "type": "link"
              },
              "name": "War of Immortals",
              "page": 69,
              "type": "source"
            }
          ],
          "text": "Options with this trait grant or utilize mythic power. Feats with the mythic trait can only be taken by mythic characters, who are typically characters with a mythic Calling.  \n  \n Monsters with the mythic trait have access to a pool of Mythic Points and are particularly strong for creatures of their level. Many mythic monsters are either resistant or entirely immune to attacks from non-mythic creatures and weapons.  \n  \n Spells with the mythic trait require the expenditure of a Mythic Point in order to be cast, and items with the mythic trait require the expenditure of a Mythic Point in order to use their activated abilities.  \n  \n Weapons with the mythic trait overcome the resistances and immunities of mythic monsters.",
          "type": "trait"
        }
      ],
      "type": "stat_block_section"
    },
